# 
data = pd.read_csv('D:\\Desktop\\.csv')

# 
data = data.dropna()

# 
X = data.drop(columns=[''])  # 
y = data['']  # 

# 
categorical_cols = ['', '', '', '', '']
encoder = OneHotEncoder(drop='first', sparse_output=False)
X_encoded = pd.DataFrame(
    encoder.fit_transform(X[categorical_cols]),
    columns=encoder.get_feature_names_out(categorical_cols)
)
X = pd.concat([X.drop(columns=categorical_cols), X_encoded], axis=1)

# 
val_cols = ['', 'CPK', '', '', '', '']
scaler = StandardScaler()
X[val_cols] = scaler.fit_transform(X[val_cols])

# float32
X = X.astype(np.float32)

# 
print("\n", X.columns.tolist())

 ['', 'CPK', '', '', '', '', '_1', '_1', '_1', '_1', '_1']

plt.title("")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# statsmodels
try:
    # VIF
    vif_data = pd.DataFrame()
    vif_data["feature"] = X.columns
    vif_data["VIF"] = [variance_inflation_factor(X.values, i) for i in range(X.shape[1])]
    vif_data = vif_data.sort_values("VIF", ascending=False)
    print("VIF \n", vif_data)
except NameError:
    print("statsmodels")

In[11]:
try:
    # VIF3
    high_vif_features = vif_data["feature"].head(3).tolist()
    
    if len(high_vif_features) >= 3:
        fig, axes = plt.subplots(len(high_vif_features), 1, figsize=(14, 10))
        axes = axes.flatten()
        for i, sort_col in enumerate(high_vif_features):
            sorted_data = data_corr.sort_values(by=sort_col).reset_index(drop=True)
            for feature in high_vif_features:
                axes[i].plot(sorted_data[feature].values, label=feature, alpha=0.7)
            axes[i].set_title(f" {sort_col} VIF")
            axes[i].set_xlabel(f" {sort_col} ")
            axes[i].set_ylabel("")
            axes[i].legend(loc="upper left")
            axes[i].grid(alpha=0.5, linestyle='--')
        plt.tight_layout(rect=[0, 0, 0.9, 1])
        plt.show()
    else:
        print("3VIF")
except:
    print("VIF")
In[12]:
# 
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=123)
print(f"{len(X_train)}{len(X_test)}")

# 
Cs = np.logspace(-3, 3, 50)  # 
log_reg = LogisticRegression(penalty='l2', solver='liblinear', random_state=123, max_iter=1000)
param_grid = {'C': Cs}

# AUC
grid_search = GridSearchCV(log_reg, param_grid, cv=5, scoring='roc_auc')
grid_search.fit(X_train, y_train)
best_C = grid_search.best_params_['C']
print(f" C: {best_C:.4f}")

20990
 C: 0.0391
In[13]:
# 
best_model = LogisticRegression(penalty='l2', C=best_C, solver='liblinear', random_state=123)
best_model.fit(X_train, y_train)

# 
y_train_prob = best_model.predict_proba(X_train)[:, 1]  # 
y_test_prob = best_model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]
y_train_pred = best_model.predict(X_train)  # 
y_test_pred = best_model.predict(X_test)

# 
auc_train = roc_auc_score(y_train, y_train_prob)
auc_test = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_test_prob)
acc_train = accuracy_score(y_train, y_train_pred)
acc_test = accuracy_score(y_test, y_test_pred)

print(f" AUC: {auc_train:.4f}, : {acc_train:.4f}")
print(f" AUC: {auc_test:.4f}, : {acc_test:.4f}")

 AUC: 0.8927, : 0.8756
 AUC: 0.8603, : 0.7556
In[14]:
# C
coefs = []
for c in Cs:
    model = LogisticRegression(penalty='l2', C=c, solver='liblinear', random_state=123, max_iter=1000)
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    coefs.append(model.coef_[0])  # 
coefs = np.array(coefs)

# 
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
for i in range(coefs.shape[1]):
    sns.lineplot(x=Cs, y=coefs[:, i], label=X.columns[i])
plt.xscale('log')  # 
plt.xlabel(' C (log)')
plt.ylabel('')
plt.title('')
plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
